I noticed that this didn't work with vanilla clang 10 from llvm.org. I'm unsure if there's some difference in paths, but vanilla clang picks up the libc++ that it's shipped with over the SDK's libc++. I suspect that distro-shipped clang's are patching default paths, which could explain why it works on some systems and not others.

I was able to fix that like this: https://github.com/theuni/bitcoin/commit/125559aac35f6ad8f6852710d3014379f8d99c4f

@dongcarl I think this is the correct fix, and I suspect it might also simplify #17920 for you. Mind having a look and pulling it in if you agree?

@dongcarl 

Multiple warnings observed on Travis macOS 10.12 [build](https://travis-ci.org/github/bitcoin/bitcoin/jobs/718179790#L3561):
`clang: warning: argument unused during compilation: '-nostdinc++' [-Wunused-command-line-argument]`
